    <h1>My Top 5 Favorite Anime</h1>

    <ol>
        <li>Attack on Titan
            <ul>
                <li>Year Released: 2013</li>
                <li>Main Characters: Eren Yeager, Mikasa Ackerman, Armin Arlert</li>
                <li>Description: In a world where humanity lives within enormous walled cities to protect themselves from gigantic man-eating Titans, a young man vows to destroy them after they bring death and destruction to his town.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>My Hero Academia
            <ul>
                <li>Year Released: 2016</li>
                <li>Main Characters: Izuku Midoriya, Katsuki Bakugo, All Might</li>
                <li>Description: In a world where nearly everyone has superpowers, a young boy born without them is determined to become a hero by enrolling in a prestigious hero academy.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Demon Slayer
            <ul>
                <li>Year Released: 2019</li>
                <li>Main Characters: Tanjiro Kamado, Nezuko Kamado, Zenitsu Agatsuma</li>
                <li>Description: A young boy embarks on a journey to become a demon slayer to avenge his family and cure his sister, who has been turned into a demon.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Death Note
            <ul>
                <li>Year Released: 2006</li>
                <li>Main Characters: Light Yagami, L, Ryuk</li>
                <li>Description: A high school student discovers a supernatural notebook that allows him to kill anyone whose name he writes in it and decides to use it to rid the world of criminals.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Fullmetal Alchemist: Brotherhood
            <ul>
                <li>Year Released: 2009</li>
                <li>Main Characters: Edward Elric, Alphonse Elric, Roy Mustang</li>
                <li>Description: Two brothers search for a Philosopher's Stone after an alchemy experiment goes wrong and leaves them in damaged physical forms.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

